"version": "1.0.4",
"title": "8821: self-indulgence",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8821",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Throwing off restraint and discipline and yielding to the desire to gratify selfish appetites and cravings. Scripture warns against such a characteristic and urges, instead, self-control, generosity and consideration for others.</p>\n<h2>The desire to satisfy selfish cravings</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:3\">EPH 2:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:8\">ROM 7:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:18\">ROM 16:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:3\">TIT 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:14\">JAS 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:18-2Pet2:19\">2PE 2:18–2:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:16\">1JN 2:16</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of self-indulgent desires</h2>\n<h3>Selfish ambition</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:14-Jas3:16\">JAS 3:14–3:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:1\">PRO 18:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:20\">GAL 5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:17\">PHP 1:17</a></p>\n<h3>The desire for one's own way</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa56:11-Isa56:12\">ISA 56:11–56:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:19\">DEU 29:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:10-Esth1:12\">EST 1:10–1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:1-Jas4:3\">JAS 4:1–4:3</a></p>\n<h3>The desire for sexual gratification</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:19\">GAL 5:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:5\">GEN 19:5</a>NUM <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:1\">25:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:8\">1CO 10:8</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:2-2Sam11:4\">2SA 11:2–11:4</a> <em>David's adultery with Bathsheba</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:11-2Sam13:14\">2SA 13:11–13:14</a> <em>Amnon's rape of Tamar</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:16-Prov7:18\">PRO 7:16–7:18</a> <em>the lure of the adulteress</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:21\">2CO 12:21</a> <em>sexual sin in the church at Corinth</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:14\">2PE 2:14</a> <em>sexual desires of false teachers</em></p>\n<h3>The desire for wealth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:3-Jas5:5\">JAS 5:3–5:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:21\">JOS 7:21</a> <em>Achan</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:3\">1SA 8:3</a> <em>Samuel's sons</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:17\">JER 22:17</a> <em>Jehoiakim, king of Judah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:4\">HAG 1:4</a> <em>the people of Judah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:11\">TIT 1:11</a> <em>false teachers in Crete</em></p>\n<h3>Indulgence in food and drink</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:13\">ISA 22:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:20\">PRO 23:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl6:7\">ECC 6:7</a></p>\n<h2>Abandoning restraint</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:19\">EPH 4:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:26-Rom1:31\">ROM 1:26–1:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:1-2Tim3:4\">2TI 3:1–3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:7\">JUD 1:7</a></p>\n<h2>The consequences of self-indulgence</h2>\n<h3>Self-indulgence proves futile</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:1-Eccl2:11\">ECC 2:1–2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:18-Luke12:21\">LUK 12:18–12:21</a></p>\n<h3>Self-indulgence leads to ruin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:17\">PRO 21:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:26\">PRO 6:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:21\">PRO 23:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:29-Prov23:32\">PRO 23:29–23:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:13-Luke15:16\">LUK 15:13–15:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:6\">1TI 5:6</a></p>\n<h3>Self-indulgence brings God's judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:8\">ROM 2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:20-Prov5:21\">PRO 5:20–5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:19\">PHP 3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:29-Dan4:32\">DAN 4:29–4:32</a> <em>God's judgment on Nebuchadnezzar's selfish pride</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:1-Amos4:2\">AMO 4:1–4:2</a> <em>God's judgment on Israel's pampered upper-class women</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos6:4-Amos6:7\">AMO 6:4–6:7</a> <em>God's judgment on Israel's self-indulgent nobility</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:19-Luke12:20\">LUK 12:19–12:20</a></p>\n<h2>Dealing with self-indulgence</h2>\n<h3>Receiving new life through Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:25\">MAT 23:25</a></strong> <em>Dealing with self-indulgence requires an inner transformation.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:2\">ROM 12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:21-Col2:23\">COL 2:21–2:23</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:14\">ROM 13:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:24\">GAL 5:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:11-Titus2:12\">TIT 2:11–2:12</a>ROM <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus8:5\">8:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:16\">GAL 5:16</a></p>\n<h3>Seeking God's will</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:36\">PSA 119:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:14\">1PE 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:2\">1PE 4:2</a></p>\n<h3>Self-control</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:3-1Thess4:5\">1TH 4:3–4:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:4\">PRO 23:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:25-1Cor9:27\">1CO 9:25–9:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:7\">1PE 4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:6\">2PE 1:6</a></p>\n<h3>Ruthless self-denial</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:5\">COL 3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:8\">DAN 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:28-Matt5:29\">MAT 5:28–5:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:11\">1PE 2:11</a></p>\n<h3>Consideration for others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:13\">GAL 5:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:23-1Cor10:24\">1CO 10:23–10:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:3-Phil2:4\">PHP 2:3–2:4</a></p>\n<h3>Generosity</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:7-Deut15:8\">DEU 15:7–15:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:8\">LUK 19:8</a></p>",
